cs.ET, cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.OL, cs.CV

The paper discusses the use of Spiking Neural Networks (SNNs) for image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed design utilizes phase-change materials (PCMs) for ultra-fast computing, which is related to the emerging technologies (cs.ET) sub-category. The use of SNNs also falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper proposes a photonic computing primitive, which is related to the architecture (cs.AR) sub-category. Finally, the proposed design leverages the inherent parallelism of wavelength-division-multiplexing (WDM), which is related to the optimization and learning (cs.OL) sub-category.
